This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the vulnerability of deep neural networks in image classification and proposes a method to generate adversarial examples. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it focuses on image classification and uses public datasets MNIST and CIFAR10. Additionally, it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the mechanism of deep learning and proposes a method to improve the defense ability. It may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with adversarial attacks and defenses. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the vulnerability of deep neural networks and proposes a method to generate adversarial examples.
